n      font-size: 14px;\n    }\n\n    th, td {\n      padding: 9px 10px;\n      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);\n      vertical-align: top;\n    }\n\n    th {\n      text-align: left;\n      background: #f1f5f8;\n      color: #24313d;\n    }\n\n    ul, ol { padding-left: 22px; }\n    li { margin: 5px 0; }\n\n    .meta { color: var(--muted); }\n    .num {\n      text-align: right;\n      font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n      white-space: nowrap;\n    }\n\n    .cards {\n      display: grid;\n      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(190px, 1fr));\n      gap: 12px;\n      margin: 16px 0;\n    }\n\n    .card {\n      border: 1px solid var(--line);\n      border-radius: 8px;\n      background: var(--panel);\n      padding: 14px 16px;\n    }\n\n    .card span {\n      display: block;\n      color: var(--muted);\n      font-size: 13px;\n      margin-bottom: 4px;\n    }\n\n    .card strong {\n      color: var(--accent);\n      display: block;\n      font-size: 22px;\n    }\n\n    .callout {\n      border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);\n      background: var(--soft);\n      padding: 12px 14px;\n      margin: 12px 0 18px;\n    }\n\n    .warnbox {\n      border-left-color: var(--warn);\n      background: #fff7ed;\n    }\n\n    .badbox {\n      border-left-color: var(--bad);\n      background: #fff5f5;\n    }\n\n    .tag {\n      display: inline-block;\n      border-radius: 999px;\n      padding: 1px 8px;\n      font-size: 12px;\n      font-weight: 650;\n      white-space: nowrap;\n    }\n\n    .ok { color: var(--good); background: #eaf7ef; }\n    .warn { color: var(--warn); background: #fff2df; }\n    .bad { color: var(--bad); background: #ffe7e7; }\n    .info { color: var(--accent); background: #e7f3f7; }\n\n    @media (max-width: 860px) {\n      header, main {\n        padding-left: 20px;\n        padding-right: 20px;\n      }\n      table {\n        display: block;\n        overflow-x: auto;\n        white-space: nowrap;\n      }\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <header>\n    <h1>Body-Tell 对齐 VoxTell v1.1 实施计划</h1>\n    <p class=\"meta\">日期：2026-05-24；目标：让 Body-Tell 在结构和权重语义上尽量对齐 VoxTell v1.1，优先支持 VoxTell checkpoint 复用，而不是只做到 tensor shape 能加载。</p>\n  </header>\n\n  <main>\n    <section>\n      <h2>核验结论</h2>\n      <div class=\"callout\">\n        <p><strong>原差异报告中的核心不一致真实存在。</strong> 其中最影响 VoxTell 权重复用的是两类问题：一类是参数量和模块拓扑明显不同，例如 encoder/decoder；另一类是参数 shape 一致但 forward 语义不同，例如 transformer decoder。</p>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"cards\">\n        <div class=\"card\"><span>Body-Tell 当前参数</span><strong>328.98M</strong></div>\n        <div class=\"card\"><span>VoxTell v1.1 参数</span><strong>440.03M</strong></div>\n        <div class=\"card\"><span>Body encoder</span><strong>8.49M</strong></div>\n        <div class=\"card\"><span>VoxTell encoder</span><strong>90.30M</strong></div>\n        <div class=\"card\"><span>Transformer 参数</span><strong>251.86M</strong></div>\n        <div class=\"card\"><span>最高风险</span><strong>shape 同而语义不同</strong></div>\n      </div>\n\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr><th>差异点</th><th>核验结果</th><th>对权重复用的影响</th><th>证据位置</th></tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Transformer decoder</td>\n            <td><span class=\"tag bad\">真实存在</span> Body-Tell 使用 <code>activation=\"gelu\"</code>，pre-norm path 执行 self-attention；VoxTell 默认 <code>relu</code>，active <code>forward_pre</code> 跳过 self-attention，只做 cross-attention 和 FFN。</td>\n            <td>参数名和 shape 可 100% 对上，但加载 VoxTell 权重后语义不等价。小模型同权重实验输出最大绝对差为 <code>0.9258</code>。</td>\n            <td><code>Body-Tell/body_tell/models/voxtell_body_model.py:69</code>、<code>Body-Tell/body_tell/models/transformer.py:137</code>、<code>VoxTell/voxtell/model/transformer.py:224</code></td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>Encoder backbone</td>\n            <td><span class=\"tag bad\">真实存在</span> Body-Tell 是 5-stage 手写 ConvBlock；VoxTell 是 6-stage <code>ResidualEncoder</code>，features 为 <code>[32,64,128,256,320,320]</code>，blocks 为 <code>[1,3,4,6,6,6]</code>。</td>\n            <td>当前 encoder 无法复用 VoxTell encoder 权重，也很可能限制性能上限。这个差异不是“轻量配置”，而是 backbone 类型不同。</td>\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_1","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/runs/SP-A.P3/RESULT.html\"","aggregated_output":"<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n  <title>SP-A.P3 Result - Replace decoder with VoxTellDecoder</title>\n  <style>\n    body { margin: 0; font: 15px/1.55 -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif; color: #17202a; background: #f6f8fa; }\n    main { max-width: 1080px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 24px 56px; }\n    section { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #d8e0e7; border-radius: 8px; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 16px 0; }\n    h1 { margin: 0 0 6px; font-size: 28px; }\n    h2 { margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 20px; }\n    p { margin: 8px 0; }\n    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 10px 0; }\n    th, td { border: 1px solid #d8e0e7; padding: 8px 10px; text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }\n    th { background: #eef3f7; }\n    code, pre { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace; }\n    code { background: #edf3f7; border-radius: 4px; padding: 1px 4px; }\n    pre { overflow-x: auto; background: #111827; color: #f8fafc; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px; }\n    .meta { color: #5d6875; }\n    .ok { color: #276749; font-weight: 650; }\n    .warn { color: #9a4a17; font-weight: 650; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<main>\n  <header>\n    <h1>SP-A.P3 - Replace decoder with VoxTellDecoder</h1>\n    <p class=\"meta\">Run date: 2026-05-24. Worker: sp_a_architecture_worker.</p>\n  </header>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Summary</h2>\n    <p>Replaced the Body-Tell custom decoder path with a Body-local <code>VoxTellDecoder</code> implementation that exposes VoxTell-compatible <code>stages</code>, <code>transpconvs</code>, <code>seg_layers</code>, and shared <code>decoder.encoder</code> state-dict structure. The model now returns five decoder outputs for a six-stage aligned encoder when <code>deep_supervision=true</code>.</p>\n    <p>The old post-upconv <code>F.interpolate</code> fallback was removed. Decoder/skip spatial mismatches now raise an explicit <code>ValueError</code>.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Files Changed</h2>\n    <table>\n      <thead><tr><th>File</th><th>Change</th></tr></thead>\n      <tbody>\n        <tr>\n          <td><code>Body-Tell/body_tell/models/voxtell_body_model.py</code></td>\n          <td>Wired <code>VoxTellBodyModel</code> to <code>VoxTellDecoder</code>; added decoder inheritance of encoder conv/norm/nonlin/dropout/bias policy; preserved always-built <code>seg_layers</code>; removed interpolation fallback.</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td><code>Body-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py</code></td>\n          <td>Added five-scale decoder output coverage, state-dict key coverage for VoxTell decoder names, always-built <code>seg_layers</code> coverage, and explicit stride-mismatch error coverage.</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td><code>Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/runs/SP-A.P3/RESULT.html</code></td>\n          <td>This result report.</td>\n        </tr>\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n    <p>No edits were made to <code>Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/lead.html</code> or <code>Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/workflow_manifest.yaml</code> for this task.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Verification</h2>\n    <h3>Requested pytest command</h3>\n    <pre><code>conda run -n voxtell python -m pytest Body-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py Body-Tell/tests/test_prompt_loss_backward.py</code></pre>\n    <pre><code>collected 11 items\n\nBody-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py .......                             [ 63%]\nBody-Tell/tests/test_prompt_loss_backward.py ....                        [100%]\n\n============================= 11 passed in 16.30s ==============================</code></pre>\n\n    <h3>SP-C deep supervision handoff smoke</h3>\n    <pre><code>PYTHONPATH=Body-Tell conda run -n voxtell python -c \"...\"\n\nnum_outputs 5\nshapes [(1, 2, 32, 32, 32), (1, 2, 16, 16, 16), (1, 2, 8, 8, 8), (1, 2, 4, 4, 4), (1, 2, 2, 2, 2)]\nloss_finite True</code></pre>\n\n    <h3>Decoder structure and parameter-count smoke</h3>\n    <pre><code>PYTHONPATH=Body-Tell conda run -n voxtell python -c \"...\"\n\nstages 5 transpconvs 5 seg_layers 5\ndecoder_params 12175429</code></pre>\n\n    <h3>Whitespace check</h3>\n    <pre><code>git diff --check -- Body-Tell/body_tell/models/voxtell_body_model.py Body-Tell/tests/test_model_shapes.py\n\nno output</code></pre>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Acceptance Checklist</h2>\n    <table>\n      <thead><tr><th>Criterion</th><th>Status</th><th>Evidence</th></tr></thead>\n      <tbody>\n        <tr>\n          <td>Model can return planned decoder outputs.</td>\n          <td class=\"ok\">passed</td>\n          <td>Shape test and smoke return five outputs: <code>32^3</code>, <code>16^3</code>, <code>8^3</code>, <code>4^3</code>, <code>2^3</code>.</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td>VoxTellDecoder structure replaces custom decoder.</td>\n          <td class=\"ok\">passed</td>\n          <td>Model exposes <code>decoder.stages</code>, <code>decoder.transpconvs</code>, five <code>decoder.seg_layers</code>, and <code>decoder.encoder.*</code> state-dict keys.</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td><code>seg_layers</code> are always built even when <code>deep_supervision=false</code>.</td>\n          <td class=\"ok\">passed</td>\n          <td>Updated test asserts trainable <code>decoder.seg_layers.*</code> parameters exist in the non-deep-supervision model.</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td>SP-C Task 5 precondition satisfied or blocker explicit.</td>\n          <td class=\"ok\">passed with explicit residual risk</td>\n          <td>Five-scale model output flows through <code>PromptSegmentationLoss</code> and backward with finite loss. Strict stride compatibility remains a data/config constraint, documented below.</td>\n        </tr>\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Blockers And Risks</h2>\n    <p><span class=\"ok\">No code blocker remains for SP-A.P3.</span></p>\n    <p><span class=\"warn\">Residual risk for full training:</span> the VoxTell-style decoder now rejects skip/upconv spatial mismatches instead of interpolating. The current aligned config declares <code>volume_size: [129, 108, 256]</code>, which is not stride-compatible with five stride-2 decoder steps. SP-C Task 5 can use the model interface now, but long training needs a stride-compatible crop/pad policy or must keep this as a data-config blocker.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Recommendation</h2>\n    <p><code>ready_for_review</code></p>\n  </section>\n</main>\n</body>\n</html>\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
